info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Advisory issued April 23 at 5:29PM CDT until April 30 at 1:00AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM CDT TUESDAY... * WHAT...Flooding caused by rain and snowmelt continues. * WHERE...Portions of Minnesota and Wisconsin, including the following areas, in Minnesota, Aitkin, Carlton, Cass, Cook, Crow Wing, Itasca, Koochiching, Lake, Pine and St. Louis County. In Wisconsin, Ashland, Bayfield, Burnett, Douglas, Iron, Price, Sawyer and Washburn County. * WHEN...Until 700 PM CDT Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. River or stream flows are elevated. Many area road closures continue. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 528 PM CDT, gauge reports indicated elevated streamflow due to rain and snowmelt. Minor flooding is already occurring in the advisory area. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
